gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 110, Knicks 105
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite Jalen Brunson's 45 points, five rebounds and four assists, the Knicks fall to the Bucks, 110-105. Damian Lillard recorded 30 points (4-7 3PM), four rebounds and four assists for the Bucks, while Giannis Antetokounmpo added 22 points, eight rebounds and six assists in the victory. Quentin Grimes tallied 17 points (5-10 3PM) for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 1-0 in East Group B play; 3-2 in the regular season, while the Knicks fall to 0-1 in East Group B play; 2-4 in the regular season.
